@component server
@intent Parent manifest of the Constellation live-board `server` family (v1.1 split per phase_2 2026-06-04 — supersedes pre-split single-file form, ~97 lines distilling 799-line server.cjs at 1:8 ratio per phase_1 G3 evaluation). The deps-0 raw HTTP + WS resident process every agent connects to. The split addresses G3/G6 from the 2026-06-03 brew-dogfooding gap catalog (large module surface-only validation + single .eux content-cramming) by separating into 4 functional sub-modules: `-core` (HTTP routes + SSE + WS upgrade + connection_role machine + envelope_convention + v2.4.11 secure-by-default boot bind policy), `-relay` (A2A relay + reply-window + telemetry + sourceStamp/targetFallback + handoff axis 2 + §13.19.10 opt-in deadlock detector), `-keys` (KEY-MGMT registry + issue/list/revoke/label, **C7 @hazards credential discipline**), `-history` (per-channel ring + streaming compression + lifecycle active/cold/archived + DB P2 thin shim delegating to history-store.eux). The `state.json` SSoT is owned by the **main** agent; the server only relays + records (workers never write the board directly — see derive `board_ssot`). Pure runtime, no DOM. Envelope convention (CUSTOM-wrapped application vs bare transport framing) is canonically anchored in `-core` `@wire`. (Re-distilled from reference @ v2.5.87, 2026-06-12 — child sub-modules re-distilled in the same pass; manifest summaries updated to match: `-core` boot bind policy + startup warnings, `-relay` §13.19.10 opt-in detector + board-inbound channel-history deletion routing, `-keys` verified already-absorbed.)
@expansion temperature=0.2 model=agent/claude template=estreux/v0.1
@targets vanilla
@profile backend-service
@source constellation/server.eux(pre-split 97 lines — promoted to manifest) split-source for 4 sub-modules · constellation/reference/runtime/server.cjs (810 lines actual @ v2.5.87, server.listen L801) — per-cluster line ranges anchored in each sub-module's @source · WS-PROTOCOL §13 orchestration · eux-format-v1.md(EstreUX commit 77e12f9 §2.5 + §4.5) split format basis
@deps
  -core: constellation/server-core.eux          # HTTP + SSE + WS upgrade + connection_role machine + envelope_convention + boot bind policy (loopback default + startup warnings)
  -relay: constellation/server-relay.eux        # A2A relay + reply-window + telemetry + sourceStamp/targetFallback + handoff + §13.19.10 opt-in deadlock detector
  -keys: constellation/server-keys.eux          # KEY-MGMT registry + lifecycle + C7 @hazards credential discipline
  -history: constellation/server-history.eux    # per-channel ring + streaming compression + lifecycle + DB P2 shim
  history-store: constellation/history-store.eux  # DB P2 mode A/B/C abstraction (dormant by default; -history delegates on operator opt-in)
@runtime
  engine: deps-0 raw HTTP + WS (no framework)
  concurrency: single-process event-loop (Node http server + ws-core handleUpgrade)
  keepAlive: SSE 20s `: ping` + WS transport-layer ping
  poll_interval_ms: 500                          # fs.watchFile state.json change detection
@redaction
  hook: pre-send + pre-log
  targets:
    - credential (full uk-/ck- key strings — see -keys @hazards for credential authority + redaction discipline)
    - PII in feedback bodies + UserPrompt content
    - real service / workspace / repo names (use generic anonymization for public traces)
    - raw tool result secret leaks (per §13.14 redaction discipline)
  authority: §13.14 reference-build redaction discipline = canonical redaction SSoT; this manifest scopes the server family
@operation_discipline
  principle: server only relays + records; main owns state.json SSoT; workers never write board (see derive board_ssot)
  derive:
    board_ssot: state.json authored by main; workers never write board directly → no multi-session collision; server is relay + storage layer only
    a2a_paired: reply-window backfills targetAgentId for adapters that can't echo A2A envelope (§13.8) — see -relay
    doc_safety: INTEGRATION_DOCS is explicit whitelist; private agreements unreachable by construction — see -core
    envelope_convention: application MUST emit CUSTOM/<name>/value{...} (3-field shape); transport framing (SERVER_HELLO/HELLO/Heartbeat/PersistentAdapterSmoke) stays bare — see -core @wire
    source_stamp_truth: server, not client, is authoritative for source role on board-fanout/record paths — see -relay
    anonymous_probe_gate: HELLO without agentId is held at transport layer but never registered (security against unauthenticated probe — see -core)
    credential_authority_split: server owns credential issuance + revoke; client gateway-client-key-mgmt exposes commands but server enforces — see -keys
    timestamp_source_stamp: record/push MUST NOT clobber timestamp on store or replay (dashboards reconstruct real wall-clock timeline) — see -history
    secure_by_default_bind: listen binds loopback unless WS_BIND explicitly opts into network exposure (boards are an unauthenticated trusted-operator surface); non-loopback → boot warning — see -core
  anti_patterns:
    - ack storm: relay does NOT auto-emit AckProcessed / ReviewSLAAck — those are agent-judgment ack tiers per §13.13 layer split
    - silent envelope mixing: bare-emitted AgentList silently drops at CUSTOM-expecting dashboard → "connected but channels empty" pitfall
    - credential log leak: full key value to non-redacted stream — see -keys @hazards redaction_discipline
    - revoke race: connection survives revoke if force-close persisted before revokedAt write — see -keys @hazards revoke_persistence_first
